The GUS Build System

INSTALLATION

1. Be sure you have Ant installed:

  % ant -help
  ant [options] [target [target2 [target3] ...]]
  Options:
    -help                  print this message
    -projecthelp           print project help information


1a. If not, see INSTALLING ANT below


2. Be sure your $JAVA_HOME variable is set:

  % echo $JAVA_HOME
  /usr/java/j2sdk1.4.0/


2a. If not, find out where your jdk is installed and set JAVA_HOME (you should
    place this in your .login or .cshrc file)


3. Set up a directory which will house your projects.  (This is where you will
   check out from cvs, and where you will edit the files you are developing.
   It is also the source for the build program).  Wherever you decide to place
   this directory, set PROJECT_HOME to it:

  % mkdir $HOME/projects
  % setenv PROJECT_HOME $HOME/projects  (place this in .login or .cshrc)


4. Set up a directory from which you will run GUS and related software.  (This
   is the target of the build program):

  % mkdir $HOME/gus_home
  % setenv GUS_HOME $HOME/gus_home  (place this in .login or .cshrc)


5. Add $GUS_HOME/bin to your path:

  % setenv PATH $GUS_HOME/bin:$PATH  (place this in .login or .cshrc)


6. If you don't already have one, set up a directory to hold your personal
   executable files, and copy install/build to there.  Add that directory to
   your path:

  % mkdir $HOME/mybin
  % cp install/build $HOME/mybin
  % chmod +x $HOME/mybin/build
  % setenv PATH $HOME/mybin:$PATH  (place this in .login or .cshrc)


7. Set up the GUS config file.

  % cp install/gus.properties.sample $HOME/.gus.properties
  % setenv GUS_CONFIG_FILE $HOME/.gus.properties (place in .login or .cshrc)


8. Edit the config file to reflect your actual values.


9. Start a new terminal session, to be sure your environment is set.


10. Give the build system a try:

  % build
usage:
  build AllGenes|Annotator|CBIL|DJob|DoTS|GUS|ParaDBs|PlasmoDB[/componentname]
install|installweb|package  targetDir -append [-co [version]]


  % build CBIL install   
